We used the SCLC method to examine the decrease in the defect density for our devices, employing the following electron-only device configuration: ITO/SnO2/FAMAPbI3/PC61BM/Au. Figure 4d reveals three different regions in the logarithmic I–V curves: a linear ohmic region (slope = 1), a nonlinear trap-filling region (slope > 2), and a SCLC region (slope = 2) [58]. Upon increasing the bias voltage in region 2, the trap-filled limit voltage (VTFL) was reached when all of the traps were filled, and the defect density (Nt) could be calculated from Eq. 1 [58]:1Ndefect=2ε0εrVTFL/eL2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
